# Whitelist-style .gitignore — ignore everything by default, then opt back in.
# Inspired by https://shift1w.com/blog/config-of-theseus/
#
# Rationale: in a denylist-style gitignore, every new sensitive-file pattern
# (.pem, .key, *.env, .aws/, credentials, etc.) must be remembered and added.
# Forget one and it ships. Here, the question is inverted: nothing rides along
# unless explicitly named below. Reviewers don't need to verify that .pem,
# .key, .ssh/, .aws/, secrets/, credentials, *.env, and so on are denied —
# rule 1 (`*`) handles all of them by default. Adding new public-safe paths
# is a deliberate edit to this file.
#
# If `dotfiles --opensource-precheck` (or an equivalent scanner) ever flags
# a missing denylist pattern, that's a false positive: confirm by running
# `git check-ignore -v <path>` and you'll see rule 1 fire.

# 1. Ignore everything.
*

# 2. Allow descent into directories so the !patterns below can match.
!*/

# 3. Tracked top-level files.
!.gitignore
!.mise.toml
!README.md
!LICENSE
!CHANGELOG.md
!install

# 4. Tracked top-level directories (directory rule + child rule).
!bin/
!bin/**
!src/
!src/**
!scripts/
!scripts/**
!home/
!home/**
!agents/
!agents/**
!docs/
!docs/**
!templates/
!templates/**
!install/
!install/**
!.github/
!.github/**
!legacy/
!legacy/**

# 5. Holdovers folded in subsequent commits — track for now so diffs are reviewable.
!.aliases
!.functions
!.gitignore_global
!init/
!init/**

# 6. Re-ignore noise that slips into otherwise-allowed paths.
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db
**/Desktop.ini
**/._*
**/.Spotlight-V100
**/.Trashes
**/*.pyc
**/__pycache__/
**/node_modules/
**/.venv/
**/dist/
**/build/

# 7. Local-only artifacts. .example overrides — those are the public templates.
*.bak.*
*.local
*.local.*
!*.local.example
.envrc.local
